The paper deals with fault-tolerant algorithms for snapshot objects in asynchronous message-passing systems, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses fault models and self-stabilization, which are relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these four categories are the most likely. Additionally, the paper involves communication costs and space constraints, which are also relevant to algorithms (cs.AL).
